    "body": "Currently bots in the examples are created with\r\n```js\r\nvar bot = mineflayer.createBot({\r\n  username: \"chatterbox\",\r\n  viewDistance: \"tiny\",\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhich means that in order to start them, it's needed to add the host and post in the code. Git is then telling us that the file change and all, not practical.\r\n\r\nI think it would be better to have something like this in all the examples : \r\n```js\r\nif(process.argv.length!=4)\r\n{\r\n\tconsole.log(\"Usage : node example.js <host> <port> <name>\");\r\n\tprocess.exit(1);\r\n}\r\nvar bot = mineflayer.createBot({\r\n\tusername: process.argv[4],\r\n\tverbose: true,\r\n\tport:parseInt(process.argv[3]),\r\n\thost:process.argv[2]});\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhat do you think ?",
